OL,3,CJoiner dragged along road by car
OL,4,Cdriven by thieves stealing his tools
OL,6,F"All of a sudden they set off with me
OL,7,Fhanging out of the car," the dad, from
OL,8,FPadiham, said. "I didn't have time to
OL,9,Fthink. I was dragged along as they
OL,10,Ftried to race off."
OL,12,FLuke eventually let go of his tool bag
OL,13,Fand was left injured in the road with
OL,14,Fcuts and grazes to his hand, shoulder
OL,15,Fand back.
OL,17,F"It could have been so much worse," he
OL,18,Fadded. "In that instant you don't
OL,19,Fthink about the consequences you just
OL,20,Freact."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
