OL,3,CJoiner dragged along road by car
OL,4,Cdriven by thieves stealing his tools
OL,6,FLuke has run his own joinery business
OL,7,FYardley Carpentry & Joinery for 13
OL,8,Fyears, and the young father suspects
OL,9,Fthat his tools will be sold for a
OL,10,Ffraction of their value to a
OL,11,Fpawnbroker.
OL,13,F"This is why I've never bought second-
OL,14,Fhand tools," he added. "You see tools
OL,15,Fin these shops with someone's name on
OL,16,Fthem, or without batteries, and it's
OL,17,Fobvious they've been nicked.
OL,19,F"If people didn't buy second-hand
OL,20,Ftools then people wouldn't steal them.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
